{
  "_name": "06 — Upscale then Crop a Region of Interest",
  "_description": [
    "MODEL REQUIRED:",
    "  NVIDIA RTX VSR model files — download the NVIDIA Video Effects SDK:",
    "  https://developer.nvidia.com/rtx-video-sdk",
    "  Verify: python scripts/check_environment.py",
    "",
    "Upscale an image 4x with RTX VSR, then crop a specific region",
    "of the upscaled result for close-up inspection.",
    "",
    "Use case: You want to check fine detail quality in a specific area",
    "(face, text, texture patch) after upscaling, without reviewing the",
    "full output at 4x resolution.",
    "",
    "Required nodes:",
    "  - RTXVSRSingleFrameNode   (our custom node)",
    "  - ImageCrop               (built-in ComfyUI node)",
    "",
    "Widget guide:",
    "  ImageCrop: x, y = top-left corner of crop region (in upscaled pixel coords)",
    "             width, height = size of crop region",
    "  Example: x=1920, y=1080, width=960, height=540",
    "           → crops a 960x540 patch from the center of a 4K upscaled image",
    "",
    "Node chain:",
    "  LoadImage ──► RTX VSR 4x ──► ImageCrop ──► SaveImage (cropped detail)",
    "                            └──────────────────────────► SaveImage (full 4x)"
  ],
